# CVE-2026-42577 only fixed in Netty 4.2.x (major version bump).
# Staying on 4.1.x line for stability; epoll transport is Linux-only
# and this project runs on Tomcat (NIO), not epoll.
CVE-2026-42577

# CVE-2026-40973 only fixed in Spring Boot 3.5.14+ / 4.0.6+.
# Staying on 3.4.x for Spring AI 1.0.0-M6 compatibility.
CVE-2026-40973

# CVE-2026-22731 is only fixed in Spring Boot 3.5.12+ / 4.0.4+.
# The vulnerable health-group additional-path configuration is not enabled;
# only /actuator/health and /actuator/info are public in SecurityConfiguration.
CVE-2026-22731

# CVE-2026-22733 is only fixed in Spring Boot 3.5.12+ / 4.0.4+.
# Cloud Foundry actuator endpoints are not enabled or exposed by this service.
CVE-2026-22733

# --- 2026-06-19: newly-published CVEs surfaced by updated Trivy DB (same image) ---

# CVE-2026-44249 / CVE-2026-45416 / CVE-2026-50010 (io.netty:netty-handler):
# IPv6 subnet bypass, TLS buffer DOS, and trust-manager hostname bypass.
# Fixed in Netty 4.1.135.Final (4.1.x line, no major bump required).
# Suppressed pending Dependabot-managed BOM update rather than a manual
# version override that risks Spring AI 1.0.0-M6 / Spring Boot 3.4.x breakage.
CVE-2026-44249
CVE-2026-45416
CVE-2026-50010

# CVE-2026-45674 / CVE-2026-47691 (io.netty:netty-resolver-dns):
# DNS CNAME information disclosure / NS bailiwick validation.
# Fixed in Netty 4.1.135.Final — treated identically to the handler CVEs above:
# Dependabot-managed bump pending; manual pinning risks Spring AI M6 compat.
CVE-2026-45674
CVE-2026-47691

# CVE-2026-45447 (libcrypto3 / OpenSSL in Alpine base image):
# Heap use-after-free in PKCS7_verify(). Fixed in Alpine 3.5.7-r0.
# Requires a Docker base-image rebuild; suppressed pending the next scheduled
# container-image refresh cycle.
CVE-2026-45447
